The pop() method removes the item at the given index from the list and returns the removed item.

The syntax of the pop() method is:

list.pop(index)







pop() parameters

The pop() method takes a single argument (index).

The argument passed to the method is optional. If not passed, the default index -1 is passed as an argument
(index of the last item).

If the index passed to the method is not in range, it throws IndexError: pop index out of range exception.











Return Value from pop()
The pop() method returns the item present at the given index. This item is also removed from the list.


